This paper is primarily focused on developing intelligent agents to solve levels in the video game Angry Birds, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses strategies for solving complex physical reasoning problems, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT) or machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for evaluating when to restart levels, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) techniques.
